Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows elevated creatinine, indicating impaired renal function, and significant proteinuria, suggesting possible nephropathy. Urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, ammoniacal odor) may indicate urinary tract pathology. Mild glycosuria and ketonuria are present despite low-normal blood glucose and low HbA1c, possibly reflecting altered renal threshold or recent dietary changes. No evidence of infection (negative nitrites/leukocytes). Recommend further nephrological evaluation and clinical correlation for underlying renal disease and urinary abnormalities.
